{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://aidazi.framework/schemas/deliver-plan-verdict.schema.json",
  "title": "Deliver milestone-decomposition verdict",
  "description": "Output shape for the Deliver Agent's milestone-decomposition conversation in the full_chain_guided bootstrap (process/delivery-loop.md §4.2.4 — guided pre-states). Decomposes the human-signed milestone brief into an ordered list of sub-sprints the Delivery Loop will execute. This verdict is ONLY parsed in loop_mode: full_chain_guided (after the Gate-1 sign-off); a charter run in delivery_only never touches it. Each sub_sprint declares the modules/layers it will touch; the driver runs a deterministic scope-expansion guard comparing the union of all sub_sprints' modules+layers against the human-signed approved_scope envelope (post-Gate-1 scope-expansion checkpoint).",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["sub_sprints"],
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "sub_sprints": {
      "type": "array",
      "minItems": 1,
      "description": "Ordered sub-sprint plan. The first entry is the one the Delivery Loop enters after decompose; subsequent entries are dispatched by the existing per-sub-sprint mechanism.",
      "items": {
        "type": "object",
        "required": ["id", "objective", "scope_in", "scope_out", "modules", "layers", "exit_criteria"],
        "additionalProperties": false,
        "properties": {
          "id": {
            "type": "string",
            "minLength": 1,
            "description": "Stable sub-sprint id (e.g. sprint-001). Referenced by dependencies + the charter's subsprint_sequence."
          },
          "objective": {
            "type": "string",
            "minLength": 1,
            "description": "One-line objective for this sub-sprint."
          },
          "scope_in": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {"type": "string"},
            "description": "What is in scope for this sub-sprint (concrete deliverables / behaviours)."
          },
          "scope_out": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {"type": "string"},
            "description": "What is explicitly out of scope for this sub-sprint."
          },
          "modules": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {"type": "string"},
            "description": "Modules this sub-sprint will touch. Their union (across all sub_sprints) is checked against approved_scope.modules_in_scope by the scope-expansion guard."
          },
          "layers": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {
              "type": "string",
              "enum": [
                "infra",
                "java_guard",
                "runtime_guard",
                "workflow_definition",
                "prompt_projection",
                "skill_state",
                "semantic_planner",
                "eval_spec",
                "product_policy",
                "judge_calibration",
                "human_review_required"
              ],
              "description": "Δ-9 fix-layer (reuses schemas/memory-entry.schema.json scope.layer enum)."
            },
            "description": "Δ-9 fix-layers this sub-sprint will touch. Their union (across all sub_sprints) is checked against approved_scope.layers_allowed by the scope-expansion guard."
          },
          "exit_criteria": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {"type": "string"},
            "description": "Observable exit criteria that close this sub-sprint."
          },
          "dependencies": {
            "type": "array",
            "items": {"type": "string"},
            "description": "Optional: ids of sub_sprints this one depends on (must precede it)."
          },
          "covered_req_ids": {
            "type": "array",
            "uniqueItems": true,
            "items": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^REQ-[A-Za-z0-9][A-Za-z0-9._-]{0,63}$"},
            "description": "Δ-19 / Constitution §1.7-F clause 1. ONLY on a gap-followup remediation sub-sprint: the in-envelope requirement ids this sub-sprint closes. The Phase 2-γ runtime req_id-envelope check proves covered_req_ids ⊆ (F1 signed snapshot ∩ the milestone's signed covers_req_ids) — DISTINCT from the module/layer scope-expansion guard. OPTIONAL + additive: absent on normal sub-sprints; every existing plan still validates."
          },
          "task_signals": {
            "type": "array",
            "uniqueItems": true,
            "items": {"type": "string", "enum": ["a11y", "design", "frontend", "interaction", "performance", "ui"]},
            "description": "Track 1 §2.3 — SIGNED task-affinity signals from the CLOSED controlled vocabulary (effective_role_config.TASK_SIGNAL_VOCAB; the enum is drift-guarded by a test) for task-aware dynamic skill mounting. This is the AUTHORITATIVE Deliver-authored source (the decompose verdict): it flows into self.state.planned_subsprints and the driver reads it per sub-sprint via _current_subsprint_plan() (so this — NOT the sprint_stanza projection — is the schema the runtime consumes). An UNKNOWN signal is schema-invalid (validate_verdict → gate_hard_fail), so signals are NEVER inferred from prose/filenames/changed-files/an LLM guess. select_skills_for_task maps these against skill-catalog `signals` tags to mount extra OPTIONAL skills for Dev/Deliver/Research/Reviewer; Acceptance is EXCLUDED (§2.5). OPTIONAL + additive: absent on every existing plan (byte-identical); planned_subsprints is NOT in the acceptance requirement-context sidecar, so this never perturbs acceptance_input_hash. Dormant until skills carry `signals` tags + Deliver authors task_signals (Track 1 Phase 1-c)."
          }
        }
      }
    }
  }
}

{
  "$schema": "https://json-schema.org/draft/2020-12/schema",
  "$id": "https://aidazi.framework/schemas/sprint_stanza.schema.json",
  "title": "Sprint stanza",
  "description": "Compact 4-field machine-validated header for docs/sprint_objective.md. Carried into v4 from csagent practice. Validated at sub-sprint dispatch (orchestrator preflight: validate_stanza gate, process/delivery-loop.md §4.2.4) and at close.",
  "type": "object",
  "required": ["sprint_id", "scope_in", "layers", "exit_criteria"],
  "additionalProperties": false,
  "properties": {
    "sprint_id": {
      "type": "string",
      "minLength": 1,
      "description": "Stable id (e.g., 'sprint-027' or 'M5-sprint-3')."
    },
    "scope_in": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {"type": "string"},
      "minItems": 1,
      "description": "Specific deliverables this sub-sprint produces. Must be subset of charter.approved_scope (scope_envelope_check, process/delivery-loop.md §4.2.5)."
    },
    "layers": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string",
        "enum": [
          "infra",
          "java_guard",
          "runtime_guard",
          "workflow_definition",
          "prompt_projection",
          "skill_state",
          "semantic_planner",
          "eval_spec",
          "product_policy",
          "judge_calibration"
        ]
      },
      "minItems": 1,
      "description": "Fix-layers this sub-sprint touches. Must be subset of charter.approved_scope.layers_allowed."
    },
    "exit_criteria": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {"type": "string"},
      "minItems": 1,
      "description": "Observable criteria for sub-sprint close. Distinct from milestone closure_contract — this is sub-sprint-level."
    },
    "modules": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {"type": "string"},
      "description": "Optional repo paths (if not enumerated, derived from charter.approved_scope.modules_in_scope ∩ scope_in)."
    },
    "milestone_id": {
      "type": "string"
    },
    "next_subsprint": {
      "type": ["string", "null"]
    },
    "covered_req_ids": {
      "type": "array",
      "uniqueItems": true,
      "items": {"type": "string", "pattern": "^REQ-[A-Za-z0-9][A-Za-z0-9._-]{0,63}$"},
      "description": "Δ-19 / Constitution §1.7-F clause 1. ONLY on a gap-followup remediation sub-sprint: the in-envelope requirement ids this sub-sprint closes. The Phase 2-γ runtime req_id-envelope check proves covered_req_ids ⊆ (F1 signed snapshot ∩ the milestone's signed covers_req_ids) — DISTINCT from the module/layer scope-expansion guard. OPTIONAL + additive: absent on normal sub-sprints; every existing stanza still validates."
    },
    "task_signals": {
      "type": "array",
      "uniqueItems": true,
      "items": {"type": "string", "enum": ["a11y", "design", "frontend", "interaction", "performance", "ui"]},
      "description": "Track 1 §2.3 — SIGNED task-affinity signals from the CLOSED controlled vocabulary (effective_role_config.TASK_SIGNAL_VOCAB; enum drift-guarded by a test) for task-aware dynamic skill mounting; the sub-sprint-doc PROJECTION of the same field. The AUTHORITATIVE Deliver-authored source the RUNTIME consumes is deliver-plan-verdict.schema.json sub_sprints[].task_signals (→ self.state.planned_subsprints → driver _current_subsprint_plan()); this stanza field mirrors it for the docs/sprint_objective.md contract and MUST agree. Authored by Deliver at decompose/sign-off — NEVER LLM-inferred from prompt text (determinism). select_skills_for_task maps these against skill-catalog `signals` tags to mount extra OPTIONAL skills for Dev/Deliver/Research/Reviewer (Acceptance is EXCLUDED — §2.5). OPTIONAL + additive: absent on every existing stanza (byte-identical); neither the stanza nor planned_subsprints enters the requirement-context sidecar → acceptance_input_hash is unaffected. Dormant until skills carry `signals` tags + Deliver authors task_signals (Track 1 Phase 1-c)."
    }
  }
}

